 Educational Background



 


Siena College

                  Siena College is an independent Roman Catholic liberal arts college in Loudonville, Albany County, New York, United States. Siena is a four-year, coeducational, independent college in the Franciscan tradition, founded by the Franciscan Friars in 1937. It has 3,200 full-time students and offers undergraduate degrees in business, liberal arts, and sciences.                




 


The City College of New York

                  The City College of New York (CCNY), the first college of The City University of New York (CUNY), is a comprehensive teaching, research, and service institution dedicated to accessibility and excellence in undergraduate and graduate education.                





 Career History



Co-Founder

                                    2005 - Current                


Bright Hub, Inc.


                  Bright Hub, Inc. provides business infra structure to software developers. Its focus areas include computing, education, mobile, science, environment, electronics, multimedia, Internet, business, finances and engineering. The company was founded by Robert Smith, Joshua Andeson McWilliam and William P. Phelan in 2006 and is headquartered in Troy, NY.                




Chief Executive Officer

                                    1999 - 2004                


OneMade, Inc.







 Boards & Committees



Corporate Boards ▾




Independent Director

                    2004 - Current                  


Mechanical Technology, Inc.

                    Mechanical Technology, Inc. engages in manufacturing, designing, and selling the test and measurement instruments and systems. The company operates through its subsidiary MTI Instruments, Inc., is a supplier of precision linear displacement solutions, vibration measurement and system balancing solutions, and wafer inspection tools. Mechanical Technology was founded by Beno Sternlicht and Harry Apkarian in 1961 and is headquartered in Albany, NY.                  




Chief Executive Officer & Director

                    Current                  


Bright Hub, Inc.

                    Bright Hub, Inc. provides business infra structure to software developers. Its focus areas include computing, education, mobile, science, environment, electronics, multimedia, Internet, business, finances and engineering. The company was founded by Robert Smith, Joshua Andeson McWilliam and William P. Phelan in 2006 and is headquartered in Troy, NY.                  




Director

                    2005 - Prior                  


MeOH Power, Inc.

                    MeOH Power, Inc. develops and manufactures cord-free rechargeable power pack technology for portable electronics. It has developed a miniaturized proprietary direct methanol fuel cell technology called Mobion. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Latham, NY.                  




Director

                    1995 - 1999                  


Florists' Transworld Delivery, Inc.

                    Florists' Transworld Delivery is a floral wire service, retailer and wholesaler based in Downers Grove, Illinois, in the United States. FTD was founded as Florists' Telegraph Delivery in 1910, to help customers send flowers remotely on the same day by using florists in the FTD network who are near the intended recipient.                  




Non-Profit Boards ▾




Director

                    Current                  


Capital District Physicians Health Plan, Inc.

                    Founded in 1984, Capital District Physicians Health Plan, Inc. (CDPHP) is a not-for-profit individual practice association (IPA) model health maintenance organization (HMO) headquartered in Albany, New York. The firm offers HMO services (AvidCare), PPO services (AchievaCare) and EPO services (AttentiCare). The CDPHP family of products includes three lines of business: (1) Capital District Physicians' Health Plan, Inc. (CDPHP) (2) CDPHP Universal Benefits, Inc. (CDPHP UBI) and (3) Capital District Physicians' Healthcare Network, Inc. (CDPHN).                  





